1.1 Food Delivery Application System
a) Functional Requirements (Food Delivery)
User registration and login.
Browse restaurants and menus.
Search food items (by name, cuisine, price).
Add items to cart.
Place order (choose address, payment method).
Online payment (UPI/Card/Wallet) and COD.
Track order status (Placed → Accepted → Out for delivery → Delivered).
Delivery partner login and view assigned orders.
Restaurant login to accept/reject orders and update status.
User can rate and review orders/restaurants.
Order history for users.
Notifications (order confirmation, delivery updates).
Non-Functional Requirements (Food Delivery)
Performance: Page load time < 3 seconds for normal load.
Scalability: Must support many users at peak (e.g., dinner time).
Security: Password hashing, secure payment (HTTPS, SSL).
Availability: System available 24/7 with minimal downtime.
Usability: Simple UI for all age groups.
Reliability: Orders should not be lost even if network problem occurs.
Maintainability: Code should be modular and easy to update.
Portability: Should work on web + Android/iOS.
  
1.2 E-Ticketing System (Train/Bus/Movies etc.)
a) Functional Requirements
User registration and login.
Search events/journeys (by date, source–destination, time).
View seat availability and price.
Book ticket and choose seat.
Online payment.
Generate e-ticket (PDF/QR code).
Cancel ticket and get refund (according to policy).
View booking history.
Admin can add/update/delete schedules.
Admin can view reports on bookings.
Non-Functional Requirements
High availability, especially during peak booking times.
Fast response (ticket booking in few seconds).
Strong security for payments and personal data.
Proper logging of all transactions.
Good usability on mobile and desktops.
Backup and recovery of booking data.

1.3 Online Banking System
Functional Requirements
Customer registration and KYC verification.
Login with username/password + OTP.
View account balance and mini statement.
Transfer money (NEFT/RTGS/IMPS) between accounts.
Add/manage beneficiaries.
View transaction history.
Pay bills (electricity, phone, etc.).
Change password, update profile
Admin/staff module to approve accounts, monitor transactions.
Non-Functional Requirements
Very high security: encryption, 2FA, session timeout.
Reliability: transactions must be correct and consistent.
Availability: almost 24/7, minimal downtime.
Performance: quick transaction processing.
Compliance: follow banking rules and regulations.
Auditability: detailed logs for all activities.

1.4 Online Course Reservation System
(You have this multiple times, so one clear list.)
Functional Requirements
Student registration and login.
Browse available courses (name, faculty, time, capacity).
Reserve/enroll in a course (if seats available).
Cancel reservation before deadline.
View current and past enrolled courses.
Admin/Faculty module to create, update, delete courses.
Set seat limit for each course.
Waitlist management (optional).
Non-Functional Requirements
System should handle many students at registration time.
Quick response for searching and reserving courses.
Proper validation to avoid overbooking.
Simple UI for students and staff.
Good data backup and recovery.
Secure access (login, session management).

1.5 Online Railway System
Functional Requirements
User registration/login.
Search trains by source, destination, date.
View seat availability and fare.
Book tickets and choose class/berth.
Online payment and ticket generation.
Cancel ticket, get refund.
PNR status check.
Admin manages trains, routes, schedules.
Non-Functional Requirements
Similar to E-Ticketing: performance, scalability, security, reliability, usability.
  
1.6 Passport Automation System
Functional Requirements
New user registration and login.
Fill passport application form.
Upload documents (ID proof, address proof, photo).
Choose appointment date and center.
Pay application fees online.
Track application status (Submitted → Verified → Approved → Dispatched).
Admin staff verify documents and update status.
Notification via SMS/Email.
Non-Functional Requirements
High security of personal identity data.
Data integrity and backup.
Good performance during peak times
Proper access control (public vs staff vs admin).
Easy-to-use interface.
  
1.7 Book Bank System / Book System
Functional Requirements
Student registration and login.
Search books (title, author, subject).
Issue book (if available).
Return book and calculate fine (if late).
View list of issued books
Librarian can add, update, delete book records.
View reports (overdue books, most issued books).
Non-Functional Requirements
Accuracy of records.
Easy and fast search.
Simple UI for librarian and students.
Backup of database.
Access control: student vs librarian.



